ISLAMABAD, Oct 25 (APP): Federal Minister for Information and Broadcasting Chaudhry Fawad Hussain said on Monday that the celebrations of Kashmiris in Illegally Indian Occupied Jammu and Kashmir after Indian cricket team’s defeat against Pakistan should be an eye opener  for the Prime Minister Modi and company.
In a tweet, he said that the way in which Muslims have once again been subjected to mental and physical torture by Modi’s stooges in India must be condemned.   He said that time has come to raise voice against Hindutva  brigade led extremism.
